description: For sale: $575,000. Welcome to the charm of Afton! Country feel with convenience of Woodbury and downtown Afton. This property has plenty of space to roam with its 16.68 Acres; add a pole barn, plant gardens or just enjoy the peace and privacy. Spacious 3 car garage with huge walk up attic storage, heated and insulated too. Classic home features main level laundry and ½ bath, 3 bedrooms up; large owners suite includes sitting area, two closets and private bath. Unfinished lower level could be finished with additional bedroom, family room and bath; bring your imagination. Newer windows, upgraded appliances, and utilities. Imagine grill outs on the deck, bonfires & fun in the backyard.  Welcome Home! We are practicing safety and health guidelines put forth by the CDC so you can feel confident about in-person showings which the seller is allowing. We are also happy to offer virtual showings at request.

description: For sale: $2,100,000. Exceptionally rare and exquisite, this rustic farmhouse-inspired rambler will astound you with its fine attention to detail and master craftsmanship of reclaimed wood throughout. Built on a private, heavily wooded 5+ acre lot on Afton's pristine Lake Edith, where peace and serenity abound, this treasured estate offers tranquil lake views from inside out and an endless list of amenities, making it an entertainer's dream. Adorned with stone, wood accents and gable roofs, the front porch is a delightful, warm welcome to the foyer, where you'll instantly discover an abundance of oversized, floor-to-ceiling windows that maximize the breathtaking views of the lake. Embellished with wood paneled ceilings and walls, the vaulted great room is a sanctuary with its stone surround gas fireplace and leads you into the gourmet kitchen, where the ambiance is warm and inviting. Farmhouse light fixtures hang from a beamed wood ceiling, while hickory cabinets surround professional appliances, and a large center island made of threshing floor pine and a striking granite counter offers additional seating next to the informal dining area. Adjacent to this space is a vaulted family room encased in white shiplap with a sliding barn door that allows you to shut out the noise and relax. Another highly desirable amenity is the formal office with sliding glass barn doors and exclusive access to the front porch. And in its own nook of the home is the private main level Owner's suite with peaceful lake views and spa-like en suite with a free-standing soaking tub, tile surround steam shower and double vanity with copper sinks. Further, a walk-thru master closet is conveniently connected to the laundry room, and to round out the main level, a spacious mudroom with gorgeous built-ins provides two access doors to the heated, pull-through garage that makes storing your vehicles and toys a breeze. The two remaining bedrooms serviced by a ¾ Jack & Jill bath can be found in the lower level, and perfect for entertaining, a large recreation room provides a theater system and impressive wet bar, complete with a TV, appliances and wrap-around seating. The walkout then leads to an outdoor oasis nestled in the wooded backyard, where you can enjoy an elevated deck, stamped concrete patios, bonfire pit and an incredibly restored party barn, along with your own dock and some of the best fishing in the Metro. Properties like this are few and far between, clearly an opportunity of a lifetime! Click here for a video tour: https://tours.spacecrafting.com/nvideo-2cqs

description: For sale: $1,450,000. Let LDK Homes build this stunning luxury home with nearly 5,500 finished sq. ft.  Custom designed with amazing quality and details throughout! Large walk-in pantry, expanded mudroom with built-ins, unique over-sized 3+ car garage, upstairs includes upper level laundry with convenient built ins and folding counters. Expansive bedroom suites and luxury master suite. Amazing lower level with full bar, rare expansive sport court with adjoining exercise room, plus a bonus theater room perfect for entertaining. Amazing location just steps away from the north side of Afton State Park. Other home options also available.

For sale: $450,000. What an amazing opportunity to own an updated historic home on 1 acre in the heart of Afton! description: For sale: $1,350,000. Pleased to present this luxurious 5bd/5ba custom-built two-story home on acreage with beautiful nature preserve views in the back. Home features an 850 sq ft sport court, storage room/bunker under the wrap-around front porch, game area/theater room, loft, and so much more. The garage is over 1,800 sq ft with a floor drain, hot/cold water in the garage and includes a 12 x 25 room on the back that can serve as a gym, woodshop, etc. 400 amp electrical service, wifi Sonos speakers inside and out, and security cameras. Custom knotty alder cabinets with granite in all bathrooms and laundry room. Beautiful coffer ceiling in the master bedroom. Option to convert sport court to the main level mother-in-law suite. Build your dream home with NewCon Homes. Your lot or ours.

For sale: $575,000. Fantastic walkout rambler with STUNNING St Croix River views. Rare Afton neighborhood setting provides the best of both worlds, privacy and neighbors! description: For sale: $1,150,000. Make this rare & historical 32 acre Afton property part of your living legacy.  Boasting beautiful rolling hills & valleys with over 800ft of the famous  Valley Creek trout stream & a large pond, this property holds the true meaning of Robert Burns "Sweet Afton". Conveniently located, close to the city of Afton, three St. Croix river marina's, public beaches, never-ending bike trails, Afton state park, Afton Alps ski-hills, & award-winning schools. Surrounded by the Belwin Conservatory, large estates, beautiful farms & low-density twnships make this a unique & highly sought after setting within a 20min drive from St. Paul. There is an abundance of wildlife of large whitetail deer, turkeys, mallards, geese, bald eagles & three different types of trout swimming in the never freezing natural spring-fed creek. This is a sportsman's & conservationists paradise! The 3 bedroom rambler includes original Anderson windows, original hardwood floors, redwood siding, wood-burning FP.

description: Recently sold: $535,000. Charming 2 story home situated on a gorgeous 5+ acre private lot in Afton.  Enjoy the stunning year round St. Croix River views from almost every room of the house. The home features 3 bedrooms, 3 bathrooms, 2 fireplaces & a 3 season porch. This property has plenty of storage for all your needs- there is a 2 car attached garage, along with an additional detached 2 car garage & workshop. The private 5 acre lot offers a mix of wooded land along with open spaces, perfect for gardening, a hobby farm or room for the kids to play!  There is also an abundance of wildlife that can be seen daily- deer, turkeys, eagles & owls just to name a few. Situated in the Afton Hills neighborhood, this home offers the perfect mix of country living combined with a small neighborhood setting. description: Recently sold: $929,000. Situated on a private, 3.2-acre lot in the scenic Cedar Bluffs Homestead neighborhood, this sensational home is surrounded by protected woodlands and prairie, offering all the peace and serenity you could ask for.  A well-thought-out floor plan and extensive windows lend tranquil views throughout, while the openness of the home makes everyday living comfortable and easy.  The entire main level living area flows from one room to the next, starting with a formal dining area off the front entrance and a two-story great room that showcases a towering, floor-to-ceiling, stone surround gas fireplace flanked by gorgeous walnut built-ins.  In addition, a wall of oversized windows and patio doors leads to an intimate screened-in porch, where you can relax on those summer and fall nights overlooking the wooded backyard and open space beyond.  A separate door from here leads to the informal dining area and spacious, gourmet kitchen that is simply stunning with its walnut cabinetry, granite countertops and coordinating tile backsplash accents.  The garage entrance is conveniently located around the corner, along with a half bath, laundry room, and handy built-in locker system and walk-in closet in the mudroom.  Down the hall, you?ll find two more bedrooms that are serviced by a full bath with a double sink vanity, making it easy to share.  On the other end of the home, is the quiet and restful master suite, where you?ll be pleased to find a sitting nook with private access to the screened porch and an outstanding bath that presents double vanities, a soaking tub, walk-in tile surround shower with dual shower heads, in-floor heat, and much-desired dual walk-in closets with built-in organization systems and private laundry.  An additional bedroom suite in the lower level is also a sanctuary, equipped with a built-in storage bench and shelving, separate study nook, lounge area, ¾ bath and another impressive walk-in closet.  The living area on this level is open and expansive, starting with a family room where you can cozy up to its wood-burning fireplace, space for a roughed-in wet bar and numerous areas for games and recreational activity.  The walkout then leads to a large patio with a hot tub that you can unwind the day in and sweeping backyard where your options are limitless year-round.  With its architectural curb appeal and mesmerizing features, this is the home you?ve been dreaming of.

description:
Recently sold: $353,000. Wonderful five bedroom/three bath walk-out rambler nestled on a private 3.2 acre wooded lot in beautiful Afton countryside. This lovely home has been completely renovated with modern details and finishes throughout and boasts a large open floor plan, hardwood floors, vaulted ceilings, skylights throughout main level; gourmet kitchen with stainless steel
appliances, nine foot center island; granite countertops, tile backsplash, soft-pull drawers and tons of storage space; three bedrooms on upper level with vaulted ceilings and skylight in each room; updated baths; huge solarium/sunroom on back of home with separate heating system and lots of sunlight offering great space for entertaining or possible nursery; finished
basement with separate entry perfect for mother-in-law suite; new cedar deck and cedar shake porch; large shed with tons of additional storage space; extra deep attached garage; amazing lot with mature trees and large areas for gardening and landscaping; peaceful country setting with lots of wildlife including deer and turkeys; ideal location close to Woodbury, shopping, restaurants and Hwy 94; new A/C, septic system, water softener and so much more! Truly unique and move-in ready! A must see!

description: Recently sold: $472,000. All brick executive rambler w/ modern open floor plan on your own private, tree-lined 5 acre hobby farm.  One-level living at its finest, with easy access into the house and main floor laundry. Huge master suite with 2 person Jacuzzi tub, stone fireplace, quiet 3.5 season heated porch overlooking stone landscaping and flower gardens.  House was remodeled in 2011 with premium Anderson windows, cherry hardwood flooring, nock-down ceiling texture, R-60 insulation, new roof, new furnace, water softener, reverse-osmosis water system, and more.  Kitchen remodeled in 2017 with butcher-block countertop, stainless steel appliances and large gas cooktop. Finished basement with office and theatre room, plenty of room for additional bedroom(s).  Attached, oversized garage is insulated & finished with floor drain and hot/cold water. Ultimate man-cave 45x30 pole barn has concrete floor, overhead doors, insulation and heat.  Lg tilled garden & fruit trees. WDBY school district w/ Afton taxes!

For sale: $450,000. What an amazing opportunity to own an updated historic home on 1 acre in the heart of Afton! This remodeled home boasts Hardie-Board siding, a newer roof, plentiful outdoor entertaining space, a 3 car garage, and much more. The vaulted master suite will give you peaceful retreat, while the upgraded kitchen allows for walk-out entertaining to the patio and deck with water feature. This prime location allows you to walk right into downtown Afton to the shops and restaurants. Close access to 94 makes for a quick commute. The private ravine is complete with trails and fire pit!
Recently sold: $225,000.

Recently sold: $932,500. Rocky Mountain Styled Lodge 
Afton, Minnesota

Residents of Afton have been drawn here by the picturesque wooded rolling hills, the deep and rugged ravines and the lure of the St. Croix River.  Most all are seeking privacy, seclusion and when possible a house that is unique in styling reflecting the individualism of the owner.

This Rocky Mountain styled home incorporates rustic materials executed with deliberate care.  Designed by local architect Jerry Allan and built by the award winning firm Vujovich Design Build, the owner?s love of a relaxful lifestyle is reflected in the open floor plan, the materials used and the stunning seven acre setting.

The home has been carefully sited at the end of the long curving blacktopped drive that winds through the wooded setting.  The house, set at tree top level, commands gorgeous views from the extensive placement of windows designed to take full advantage of the site.  No other homes are visible from this secluded site surrounded by 90 acres of undevelopable land on the east and 35 acres of deep ravine land on the south.

The exterior of the home is constructed of pine finished with Sikkens, a high quality wood preservative.  Stone accents have been used for support pillars and the foundation.  Beautifully, but minimally landscaped, maintenance is not time consuming.

The interiors are magazine beautiful!  An open or great room concept has been utilized with all main level living spaces flowing together.  Vaults, massive beams, locally milled random sawn pine flooring with decorative nail detail and distressed alder wood cabinetry combine for a warm and inviting space that draws you to the dry stack stone wood burning fireplace for conversation or relaxation.  A full wall of windows and an exterior deck have been placed across this space enabling dramatic views.

A main level owner?s suite is on this level and is complete with walk-in closet in which, conveniently  located is a washer/dryer.  A private bath with separate tub and shower and double sink vanity are intended for the exclusive use of the occupants of this suite.  The same quality materials have been incorporated.  Rough sawn cedar has been used on the vaulted ceiling with Durango stone, limestone and slate finishing the bath.  Rimless shower doors are in place.  A private deck off the owner?s suite offers a quiet retreat overlooking the wooded hilltop site.  Wired for speakers, a new owner may create a musical ambiance for relaxation.

The lower level includes a large gathering area.  A conversation grouping in front of a second dry stack gas fireplace anchors one area with a billiard/game/section anchoring the other.

There are three bedrooms on this lower level with a full bath and half bath.  The half bath has been plumbed to expand with shower or tub.  A bar area has also been plumbed for a future entertainment opportunity.

There are two separate garages for this home; one serving the main level, the second (located under the upper garage) accessed from the lower level.  The lower garage is heated and ventilated with its own air exchanger with wiring in place for satellite TV. A separate stair system offers direct access from the upper garage to the lower.

There are too many unique features to mention in this brief narrative such as the custom designed railings for the stair system.  The unique light fixtures that have been selected and on and on.  Suffice it to say that if a newer rustic flavored house set among the dramatic bluffs of Afton says home to you, do schedule a showing and fall in love with this very special property.  Please visit: www.ROCKYMTNLODGE.net
